# <project-name>

## Overview

`<project-name>` is a full-stack application scaffolded with the Forge framework's
`full-stack-monorepo` archetype. It consists of three layers: a Flutter frontend, a
Rust backend, and an infrastructure layer (Envoy Gateway + Kubernetes + Temporal + Docker).
Protobuf definitions in `shared/protos/` are the single source of truth for all
cross-layer contracts.

## Architecture

```text
<project-name>/
├── frontend/         # Flutter — FSD + Clean Architecture
├── backend/          # Rust — Cargo workspace, hexagonal
├── infra/            # Envoy Gateway + K8s + Temporal + Docker
├── shared/protos/    # Protobuf contracts (source of truth)
├── .forge/           # Forge framework assets
├── .claude/          # Claude Code agents, commands, skills
├── Taskfile.yml      # task dev/test/lint/proto/release
└── docker-compose.dev.yml
```

- `frontend/` — Flutter app using Feature-Sliced Design + Clean Architecture.
- `backend/` — Rust Cargo workspace organised as a hexagonal (ports & adapters) monolith.
- `infra/` — Envoy Gateway (Kubernetes Gateway API), Kubernetes manifests, Temporal workflows, Docker files.
- `shared/protos/` — Buf-managed `.proto` files; never duplicated in layer code.
- `.forge/` / `.claude/` — Forge pipeline assets and Claude Code routing rules.

## Prerequisites

Install the following tools before running anything locally:

- **Flutter ≥ 3.24** — <https://docs.flutter.dev/get-started/install> (`flutter --version`)
- **Rust ≥ 1.80** — <https://www.rust-lang.org/tools/install> (`cargo --version`)
- **Buf ≥ 1.30** — <https://buf.build/docs/installation> (`buf --version`)
- **Docker + Docker Compose** — <https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/> (`docker compose version`)
- **Task (go-task)** — <https://taskfile.dev/installation/> (`task --version`)

## Quickstart

1. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone <repo-url> <project-name> && cd <project-name>
   ```

2. Copy the environment file and fill in local values:

   ```bash
   cp .env.example .env
   # edit .env with your editor
   ```

3. Start the compose stack (Postgres + backend):

   ```bash
   task dev:up
   ```

4. Regenerate Protobuf stubs after any `.proto` change:

   ```bash
   task proto
   ```

5. Run all layer tests:

   ```bash
   task test
   ```

6. Run the Flutter frontend:

   ```bash
   cd frontend && flutter run
   ```

## Development workflow

- All code changes go through the Forge pipeline:
  `/forge:new` → specify → design → plan → implement → review → archive.
  Read `.forge/constitution.md` for the non-negotiable rules.
- Commit messages **must** use scoped Conventional Commits. Allowed scopes:
  `backend`, `frontend`, `infra`, `protos`, `forge`, `docs`, `ci`.
  See `.forge/standards/global/git-workflow.md` for the full policy.
- Cross-layer changes (touching ≥ 2 layers simultaneously) are routed through
  **Janus** — see root `CLAUDE.md` for the routing policy.

